## What I Did This Week

This week I focused on improving how I communicate at work, both verbally and in writing.

### Daily Stand-Up Meetings
- Joined the team's daily stand-up meetings every morning
- Gave a short update about what I was working on each day
- Kept my updates short, clear, and easy to understand

### Talking to My Supervisor
- Explained any problems or blockers to my supervisor using simple words
- Avoided using too many technical terms so the message was clear
- This helped my supervisor understand the issue quickly and give me the right guidance

### Writing Notes and Documentation
- Started writing simple notes about the code I worked on
- Made sure the notes were easy for other team members to read and follow
- Took notes during team meetings to keep track of what was discussed and decided
- Shared the meeting notes with the rest of the team

### README Template
- Created a basic README template for the project
- The template included sections for project description, setup steps, and notes
- The team started using this template for the project

